   This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  "Normally the reason why we award medals it is for South Africans to appreciate and also to say thank you to those who work tirelessly, excellently and diligently in the service of our nation," he said.  
"I would like to thank you for your service and professionalism because it is expected of us as custodians of the security of this country that we conduct ourselves in a professional manner and professionalism goes a long way. It is something that requires discipline, loyalty and dedication," he told the recipients.  
He added that medals served as an encouragement and motivation. 
